There's nothing like new hair to make you feel confident and beautiful.

Hair represents “confidence “, confidence represents “strength “
With all forms of alopecia, your body’s own immune system attacks your healthy hair follicles, causing them to become much smaller and drastically slow down production to the point that hair growth may stop.

Depending on which type and severity of the disease you have, you might experience hair loss in different areas and your hair loss and regrowth may be unpredictable and cyclical (happening over and over) for many years. Though for some people, hair may also regrow in a few months.
Most cases like this take a multi modality approach and results like these take several months to even a year!

This transformation video shows the magic we do to our patients through our hair regrowth treatments 😍

Look at that nose transformation in just one session of Hydrafacial MD treatment😍

If you are looking for flawless, beautiful skin on top of your usual skin regime, you can opt for our HydraFacial treatment. 

HydraFacial treatments are recommended throughout the year, no matter the climatic conditions.

The process of HydraFacial follows 3 steps: 

- Cleanse & Peel: Using a gentle exfoliation, this step uncovers a new layer of skin. 
- Extract & Hydrate: This step removes extra debris from your pores and nourishes your skin.

- Fuse & Protect: Lastly, we saturate your skin with antioxidants and peptides, which achieves a beautiful and youthful glow. 
For long-term results, multiple sessions may be required. It is recommended to do at least three sessions monthly once to start noticing a visible change.

We use the authentic HydraFacial MD device, which is the gold standard across the globe 🌎

FOUR PROVEN TECHNOLOGIES:

1. LED LIGHT THERAPY Red (630nm), Blue (460nm) & Green (520nm)

The beneficial wavelengths of Light Emitting Diode Therapy (LED) have been proven and shown to improve the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, fight bacteria that leads to acne, reduce redness and promote brightening and even skin tone.

Recent studies indicates, bi-weekly LED Therapy for a small interval is more effective than doing it once a month. 

2. ION CARE (Positive & Negative)

Gently, yet effectively, positively charged ions work to attract and pull impurities from the skin while negatively-charged ions enhance product penetration.

3. ULTRASONIC VIBRATION (8500 pulses per minute) 

Ultrasonic vibrations leads to breaking up the dead skin cells, lifting, firming and tightening of the skin.

4. HEAT THERAPY(Temperature of 40°C - 45°C)

The combination of heat with the deep cleansing ions aids in emulsifying dirt and oil so that it can easily be swept away. Thermal heat therapy has also been shown to improve with skin tightening, promoting more oxygen to the cells by improving blood circulation and the reducing appearance of pore size.

My heart is full today.

We were able to fly in 7 family members of 4 of our North East team — many of whom hadn’t seen each other in nearly two years. Watching them reunite, right here in our clinic, reminded me what real joy looks like. Quiet hugs. Teary eyes. Soft laughter. The kind of love that doesn’t need words.

This isn’t just about a gesture. It’s about belonging.
Because when someone leaves their home to come work with you — their dreams become tied with yours. And their families, in many ways, become part of your extended one too.

We’ve also quietly created something that means a lot to us — an Emergency Staff Fund, where we set aside money every month to support any teammate or their family in times of need. Because we believe showing up for each other shouldn’t just be an idea. It should be a system.

Today was special.
And I’m endlessly proud of what we’re building. Of our team. Of Nishita.
Of the love that holds it all together.

🧠 Dermatologist Propaganda I Fully Swear By: 

1.Sunscreen is a non-negotiable. SPF is my religion. Reapply like your collagen depends on it—because it does.

2. Skincare is healthcare.
It’s not vanity—it’s barrier repair, microbiome balance, pigment regulation, and mental wellness.

3.Tweakments > Transformations.
Subtle. Natural. Undetectable. The best work is the one no one knows you had done.

4.No facial can replace a laser.
Facials are relaxation. Lasers are results. Combine wisely.

5.You cannot out-treat poor skincare.
No amount of PRP, filler, or lasers will work if your barrier is fried and your cleanser is wrong.

6.Science-backed > Hype-backed.
Show me the ingredients, not just the influencers. 

7.Botox is preventive, not reactive.
Early intervention saves expression lines from becoming etched regrets.

8.Nothing replaces a dermatologist.
Not your facialist. Not your cousin’s DIY tips. Not your 15-step K-beauty haul.

9.Skin tells a story—treat the chapter, not just the sentence.
Pigmentation? Might be hormonal. Acne? Might be PCOS. Aging? Might be lifestyle.

10.Glow is a strategy, not a fluke.
It’s planned. Layered. Calibrated. And yes, it includes internal health.

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s proof that stress affects skin and hair: 

🧪 1. Acne Breakouts
	•	Stress increases cortisol, which boosts oil (sebum) production → clogged pores & acne.

💇‍♀️ 2. Hair Fall / Telogen Effluvium
	•	Stress pushes hair into the resting phase, causing excessive shedding 2–3 months later.

🔥 3. Eczema, Psoriasis & Rosacea Flares
	•	Stress disrupts immune balance and skin barrier → flare-ups in chronic skin conditions.

🧠 4. Itching & Hives (Urticaria)
	•	Stress releases substance P & other neuropeptides → inflammation and itching.

⏳ 5. Delayed Wound Healing
	•	High cortisol slows down collagen production → slower skin repair.

🧴 6. Dry, Dull & Sensitive Skin
	•	Stress reduces skin’s ability to retain moisture and protect itself → more dryness & irritation.

🧑‍⚕️ 7. Autoimmune Skin Triggers
	•	Conditions like vitiligo and lichen planus often worsen after emotional stress.

🤯 8. Skin Picking / Hair Pulling
	•	Disorders like trichotillomania and excoriation are strongly linked to anxiety and stress.

I literally tell every patient of mine about the impact of stress & tension on their skin & hair conditions and how managing that is important for outcome of my treatment.

Send this to someone who needs proof ↗️

Trend Watch: Decoding Viral Skincare Buzzwords!

	1.	Skin Fasting – Hitting pause on skincare to let your skin “reset.” Think of it as intermittent fasting, but for your face. Ofcourse you need to use your CMS! 

	2.	Skin Cycling – Rotating actives (like retinol, exfoliants, hydrators) on a 4-day schedule to avoid overdoing it and keep skin happy.

	3.	Skin Flooding – Layering hydrating serums on damp skin to deeply drench it in moisture. A lifesaver for dry, sensitive skin.
Love using HA serums for this. 

	4.	Skin Slugging – Sealing in your nighttime routine with a thick occlusive (like petroleum jelly) to lock in moisture. Do not try this if you have oily or acne prone skin. 

	5.	Skin Streaming – The latest one: simplifying your skincare to just 2-3 essential steps that work. Less is more! Have more & more patients requesting for this. 

Which one are you trying next? Or are you team “no trend, just science”?
